text: you
the Raven himself is hoarse that croaks
the fatal entrance of Duncan under my
battlements
you spirits that tend on mortal thoughts
unsex me here and fill me from the crown
to the toe top-full of direst cruelty
make think in my blood stop up the
access and passage to remorse that no
compunctious visitings of nature shake
my fell purpose nor keep peace between
the effect and it come to my woman's
breasts and take my milk for gall you
murdering ministers wherever in your
sightless substances you wait on
nature's mischief come thick night and
pall thee in the dummest smoke of hell
that my keen knife see not the wound it
makes nor heaven peep through the
blanket of the dark to cry hold hold
